{{Infobox journal | title = European Romantic Review | image = <!-- or |cover= --> | image_size = | alt = | caption = | former_name = <!-- or |former_names= --> | abbreviation = <!-- ISO 4 abbreviation --> | bluebook = <!-- For law journals only --> | discipline = [[interdisciplinary]] | peer-reviewed = | language = English | editor = <!-- or |editors= --> | publisher = [[Routledge]] | country = | history = 1990 to present | frequency = Bimonthly | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = | ISSNlabel = | ISSN = 1050-9585 | eISSN = 1740-4657 | CODEN = | JSTOR = | LCCN = | OCLC = | website = http://www.tandfonline.com/toc/gerr20/current | link1 = http://publish.uwo.ca/~nassr/err.html | link1-name = Journal at NASSR | link2 = <!-- up to |link5= --> | link2-name = <!-- up to |link5-name= --> | boxwidth = }}
'''''European Romantic Review''''' ('''''ERR''''') is a scholarly [[peer-review]] journal founded in 1990 and devoted to the [[interdisciplinary]] study of nineteenth-century culture.
The journal was co-founded by the poet and literary critic [[Kelly Grovier]]. Published six times a year by [[Taylor & Francis]], ''ERR'' is closely linked with [[North American Society for the Study of Romanticism|NASSR]] (The North American Society for the Study of Romanticism).
==External links== * [http://www.tandfonline.com/toc/gerr20/current European Romantic Review homepage] * [http://www.ingentaconnect.com/content/routledg/gerr Online archive of journal]
