{{publishing-stub}}

The '''Garuli''' were an ancient [[Ligures|Ligurian]] tribe mentioned by [[Livy]] as being subjugated by [[ancient Rome|Rome]] under consuls [[Marcus Aemilius Lepidus (consul 187 BC)|Marcus Aemilius Lepidus]] and [[Quintus Mucius Scaevola (consul)|Quintus Mucius Scaevola]] in 175 BCE.<ref>[[William Smith (lexicographer)|Smith]], [[Dictionary of Greek and Roman Geography]] (1857), s.v. ''Ligures''</ref> (Liv. xli. 19.) They inhabited the area of Cenisola.<ref>J. Murray, The Academy (1880), vol. 18, p. 33.</ref>
