'''''Lumooja''''' is a [[Finnish language|Finnish]] cultural and literary magazine based in [[Turku, Finland]].<ref name="ane">{{cite news|title=Lumooja|url=https://anewstip.com/outlet/profile/bsan55611358/?tab=journalists|accessdate=4 April 2017|work=Anewstip}}</ref> It features poetry and other literary work as well as articles on arts and book reviews.<ref name="ane"/>
==History and profile== The magazine was started in 2000.<ref>{{cite web|title=Lumooja: kirjallisuuslehti|url=https://jyu.finna.fi/Record/jykdok.840698|work=University of Jyväskylä - JYKDOK|accessdate=4 April 2017|language=Finnish}}</ref><ref name="turs"/> The magazine is published by a Turku-based organization, Kapustarinta (The Golden Plover Association).<ref name="turs"/> From 2000 to 2001 [[Jenni Haukio|Jenni Elina Haukio]], the wife of [[Sauli Niinistö]], [[Finnish President]], was the editor of ''Lumooja''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Jenni Elina Haukio|url=http://www.tpk.fi/public/default.aspx?nodeid=44815&culture=en-US&contentlan=2|work=Office of the President of the Republic of Finland|accessdate=4 April 2017}}</ref> Heidi Laine also served in the post, who was named as editor in 2007.<ref name="turs">{{cite news|title=Heidi Laineesta Lumoojan uusi päätoimittaja|url=http://www.ts.fi/kulttuuri/1074176242/Heidi+Laineesta+Lumoojan+uusi+paatoimittaja|accessdate=4 April 2017|work=Turun Sanomat|date=26 January 2007}}</ref> Elina Laine is the editor-in-chief of the magazine.<ref name="ane"/>
